1Ô∏è‚É£ Dataset Generation Strategy

Created 5 correlated financial assets

Used Cholesky decomposition to introduce cross-asset correlation

Simulated GARCH-like volatility clustering

Included:

Non-stationarity

Drift

Volatility shocks

Generated 2500 time steps

2Ô∏è‚É£ Feature Engineering

For each asset:

Returns (momentum)

10-day moving average (short trend)

30-day moving average (long trend)

Rolling volatility (risk)

This helps LSTM learn trend, momentum, and risk dynamics

3Ô∏è‚É£ LSTM Architecture
Layer	Units	Purpose
LSTM	128	Capture long-term dependencies
Dropout	0.3	Prevent overfitting
LSTM	64	Higher-level abstraction
Dense	32	Non-linear feature learning
Output	1	Predict Asset_0 future value

Tuning Choices

Lookback window: 30

Batch size: 32

Early stopping used

Adam optimizer

4Ô∏è‚É£ Baseline Model

We used SARIMAX(1,1,1):

Captures linear autoregressive patterns

Serves as traditional statistical benchmark

Cannot model nonlinear cross-asset dependencies like LSTM

5Ô∏è‚É£ Validation Strategy

Chronological train-test split (no leakage)

80% training, 20% testing

Validation split inside training for early stopping

